.nS note
A DSA process is also listed as a \*LDir-User\*O process type if it chains a
request through \*LS-Stub\*O to a remote DSA. \*LC-Stub\*O and
\*LS-Stub\*O are also listed as \*LDir-User\*O in the startup
phase if they are trying to read the PSAP address from the DUA cache.
.nE
.P
If the \*Lgdsdirinfo\*O command is called when the GDS is
inactive, the following message is written to \*Lstderr\*O:
.P
.oS
A shmget system call has failed (key = 1148635637,\\
access mode = 666, errno = 2).
.oE
.P
If the command executes successfully, the exit value 0 (zero) is returned;
otherwise, the value is 1 or 2.
.P
