.H 3 "Interpreting Log Files By Using gdsstep"
.ix "\*Lgdsstep\*O program"
.iX "Global Directory Service commands" "\*Lgdsstep\*O"
Logging files that are generated by GDS applications can be subsequently
evaluated and displayed with the \*Lgdsstep\*O program.  The
logging records can be used by application programmers to debug their
applications, and by users to determine network problems or protocol
problems with remote systems.
.P
For a detailed description, see the \*Lgdsstep\*O reference page.
